name: Head Ram
description: Use your head, non-metaphorically.

name: Nibble
description: Many Temtem have this habit of gently chewing plants and furniture. This is a little less gently.

name: Kick
description: Primal and instinctive, sometimes a good kick is all you need.

name: Shy Shield
description: Some Temtem are naturally introverted and keep to themselves. DEF +1.

name: Tentacle Whip
description: Tentacles. Why did it have to be tentacles?

name: Strangle
description: Strangler and strangled, united in a deadly embrace. Both attacker and target lose their next turn.

name: Cheer Up
description: Lifts the spirits of the target and reduces its Hold by 1.

name: Peck
description: All beaked Temtems like to playfully peck their tamers. This is the less friendly version.

name: Jaw Strike
description: Temtem with powerful jaws always know how to use them...

name: Held Anger
description: All that suppressed rage keeps building up... until it bursts in a nova of wrath.

name: Tail Strike
description: Sweep the board at one fell swoop,

name: Heavy Blow
description: Effective and unsubtle, like a Tucmani mine drill.

name: Fierce Claw
description: Raw as untamed Temtem and unstoppable as a Kisiwan stampede.

name: Scratch
description: Almost any claw or nail can scratch the surface. Sometimes that's enough.

name: Tenderness
description: Really? Are you going to attack something *this* cute? You deserve that ATK -1.

name: Multiple Pecks
description: A rapid-fire flurry of furious beaks.

name: Shrill Voice
description: Widely used by Accademia teachers, this Neutral attack defeans the whole class... eh, team.

name: Cooperation
description: Team equality! This equalises all team member's STA with the team average.

name: Finbeat
description: Also known as "siren slap". Hurts your pride more than anything else.

name: Photosynthesis
description: Nature Temtem are unique in their use of Pan-sunlight to nourish themselves (Recover 25% STA).

name: Sharp Leaf
description: Evolution has armed Nature Temtem with advanced defenses against herbivores.

name: Aqua Stone
description: "An ingenious application of hydraulic pressure for ballistic purposes" (Sophia d'Arissola).

name: Bubbles
description: Bubbles! <3 This weakens the target by means of extreme cuteness.

name: Pressure Wash
description: An industrial-grade water jet that packs real punch.

name: Water Blade
description: Whipping seawater, like the stormy Sillaro lashing at the cliffs.

name: Water Cannon
description: The strongest Sillaro current has nothing on this unstoppable jet.

name: Sharp rain
description: Rather like snow, if snow was razor-sharp ice needles instead of gentle flakes.

name: Tsunami
description: Summon a rarely seen tidal wave that damages a whole team.

name: Ice Cubes
description: An extreme version of the ice water bucket challenge that does real damage.

name: Chain Lightning
description: This miracle of Electric manipulation bounces 3 times clockwise, dealing decreasing damage.

name: DC Beam
description: Lightning, an elemental force - not extremely powerful, but always reliable.

name: Sparks
description: Nothing perks you up like a spark-up! (SPATK +1).

name: Tesla Prison
description: An electromagnetic trap that does light damage and slows down the target (SPD -1).

name: Bamboozle
description: Give'em the old razzle dazzle! (Target avoids the next Technique or attacked directed at it).

name: Hypnosis
description: A mind hack developed by Arubian Mind specialists, makes the target asleep for 2 turns.

name: Psy +
description: "Mens sana in corpore sano"... but the other way around.

name: Stare
description: This Temtem's intimidating stare makes rivals feel more vulnerable (DEF -1).

name: Narcoleptic Hit
description: A potent attack that exhausts the attacker's psyche, making it Asleep for 2 turns.

name: Telekinetic Shrapnel
description: Reportedly feels "like combing your brain with concertina wire."

name: Beta Burst
description: A mighty beta-wave surge that bombards the target with a subatomic fusillade.

name: Intimidation
description: That "don't mess with me" look makes the Temtem untargetable for the next turn

name: Sand Splatter
description: A fistful of humble sand becomes a faceful of dirty fighting.

name: Stone Wall
description: The best way to stonewall a Temtem, bestowing DEF +2, SDEF +1.

name: Wind Blade
description: Lashing gales, like the frozen tramontane howling over Loch.

name: Wind Burst
description: A terrifying gust of wind, capable of throwing a small airship off-course.

name: Feather Gattling
description: "Even the softest feather becomes potent when used wisely." - Miyako proverb.

name: Nimble
description: Through rigorous training, Temtem can become extra fast (SPD +1).

name: Blizzard
description: Cold and furious like the mistral winds in the Thalassian Cliffs.

name: Cold Breeze
description: A shivery draft that deals light damage and inflicts Cold for 2 turns.

name: Mirror Shell
description: "Mirror, mirror in my hand, who wants to have SPDEF +2?"

name: Glass Blade
description: Like death by a thousand cuts... but this is just one of them

name: Crystal Dust
description: A miniature version of the "star-rain" that is said to have spawned the Archipelago.

name: Crystallize
description: Inspired by the ruins of the Amethyst Barrens, this crystal crust provides DEF +2 but SPD -1.

name: Rage
description: The red mist makes a Temtem brutal (ATK +2) but also careless (DEF -2).

name: Martial Strike
description: All Melee Temtem are trained to perform this basic but effective attack.

name: Head Charge
description: There are many clever uses for a large skull. This is not one of them - but it's effective.

name: Show Off
description: A good Melee fighter is a good showman. Show off and increase ATK +1

name: Uppercut
description: Melee Temtem are all about raw strength. This technique is its sincerest expression.

name: Toxic Ink
description: The victim will have 4 poisoned turns to regret getting this tattoo...

name: Toxic Spores
description: Toxic-carrying spores that inoculate with Poison for 3 turns.

name: Urushiol
description: The substance known as Urushiol is a virulent toxic agent.

name: Venomous Claws
description: When the look of your claws doesn't prevent the fight, the poison finishes it.
